1
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,291
- I was late.
- It's okay, sweetie,

2
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:36,946
- it's not your fault.
- I just wanted to play

3
00:00:36,970 --> 00:00:37,994
one more game at Gary's.

4
00:00:38,071 --> 00:00:40,370
What? You did great,
you called 911 right away.

5
00:00:40,474 --> 00:00:42,033
- He looks dead.
- Daddy's not dead.

6
00:00:42,142 --> 00:00:43,474
He's gonna be okay, right?

7
00:00:43,544 --> 00:00:45,308
- He had a stroke.
- That's not possible.

8
00:00:45,379 --> 00:00:47,211
Well, the CT confirmed
a ruptured aneurysm.

9
00:00:47,314 --> 00:00:48,725
We have to operate
to clip the bleeding

10
00:00:48,749 --> 00:00:51,561
- and reduce intracranial pressure.
- No, he had a stroke six years ago.

11
00:00:51,585 --> 00:00:52,883
They put him on diltiazem.

12
00:00:53,754 --> 00:00:55,274
We're gonna take
good care of your dad.

13
00:00:58,392 --> 00:00:59,826
Naja Modi, 28 years old,

14
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:03,557
suffered a burn to her left hand
as a result of a cooking accident.

15
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:05,426
Are Jared and I being punished?

16
00:01:08,502 --> 00:01:11,563
This is not a very
interesting case, is it?

17
00:01:11,939 --> 00:01:12,998
Lesson one.

18
00:01:13,540 --> 00:01:17,204
Don't suggest to the head of Surgery
that working with the head of Surgery

19
00:01:17,611 --> 00:01:18,738
is a form of punishment.

20
00:01:18,845 --> 00:01:22,543
Dr. Melendez is very
unhappy with Jared

21
00:01:22,616 --> 00:01:24,175
for how he got his job back.

22
00:01:24,351 --> 00:01:29,221
And Dr. Melendez is unhappy
with me for taking two days off...

23
00:01:29,289 --> 00:01:31,758
I don't think he wants
to talk about this, Shaun.

24
00:01:36,463 --> 00:01:37,522
I was an idiot.

25
00:01:37,965 --> 00:01:40,127
It's on the stove. Of
course, it's hot, right?

26
00:01:40,434 --> 00:01:42,914
You wouldn't believe how often
we see these types of accidents.

27
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:44,470
Well, there are a lot of idiots.

28
00:01:44,638 --> 00:01:46,402
Okay. What do we
need to do here, Murphy?

29
00:01:46,873 --> 00:01:50,935
A superficial partial-thickness burn
should be managed conservatively.

30
00:01:51,044 --> 00:01:53,036
Cleanse the area,
debride with soft gauze,

31
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:56,572
and then cover with an
antimicrobial petroleum dressing.

32
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:59,549
All of which means this should
heal with minimal scarring.

33
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:03,068
Naja, are you having chest pain?

34
00:02:03,724 --> 00:02:06,091
I think I'm having a heart
attack. It's hard to breathe.

35
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:07,787
Just relax if you can.

36
00:02:09,296 --> 00:02:12,266
Put her on oxygen, a 12-lead EKG,
and order a portable chest X-ray.

37
00:02:12,432 --> 00:02:13,552
Murphy, let's move. Come on.

38
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,501
Her vitals are stable.

39
00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:23,240
- What the hell's going on here?
- I don't know. But it is interesting.

40
00:02:36,857 --> 00:02:38,234
We've got a
subarachnoid hemorrhage.

41
00:02:38,258 --> 00:02:40,454
Suction. I need to
isolate the aneurysm.

42
00:02:42,429 --> 00:02:45,524
Poor kid. Imagine
finding your dad like that.

43
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:47,795
Well, that's exactly
how I wanna die.

44
00:02:50,103 --> 00:02:51,180
If the dad doesn't make it,

45
00:02:51,204 --> 00:02:52,832
the kid will always
remember that moment,

46
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,099
be traumatized by it.

47
00:02:54,207 --> 00:02:55,266
Because he loves him.

48
00:02:55,876 --> 00:02:57,796
The idea of dying without
anybody getting hurt...

49
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:00,805
There's nothing sadder
than an empty waiting room.

50
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:05,045
Okay, what do you see?

51
00:03:05,886 --> 00:03:08,481
A bulge on the anterior
communicating artery.

52
00:03:08,555 --> 00:03:10,683
Yeah, the ruptured aneurysm
is compromising blood flow

53
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:11,815
to the frontal lobe.

54
00:03:11,992 --> 00:03:13,620
Prep an eleven-millimeter
standard clip.

55
00:03:14,661 --> 00:03:16,391
- Are you married?
- Not anymore.

56
00:03:17,130 --> 00:03:19,031
Turns out he had even
worse judgment than I did.

57
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:21,866
Speaking of creeps. You
hear Coyle got transferred?

58
00:03:21,968 --> 00:03:24,233
I'm so glad they shut him down.

59
00:03:24,838 --> 00:03:25,862
Yeah, I guess.

60
00:03:26,673 --> 00:03:29,040
Just wish they'd spent the
money on a pediatric trauma pod.

61
00:03:31,812 --> 00:03:32,905
They gave him a raise.

62
00:03:35,082 --> 00:03:36,141
Clip.

63
00:03:37,651 --> 00:03:40,849
The EKG confirmed you
weren't having a heart attack.

64
00:03:41,021 --> 00:03:43,581
I wasn't faking. I
wouldn't do that.

65
00:03:43,724 --> 00:03:44,748
We know.

66
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:46,098
The imaging also confirmed

67
00:03:46,193 --> 00:03:47,953
that you have considerable
lung inflammation.

68
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:49,381
Is it possible you
inhaled smoke?

69
00:03:49,596 --> 00:03:50,825
Well, I guess I must have.

70
00:03:51,364 --> 00:03:52,730
There was a minor grease fire.

71
00:03:53,366 --> 00:03:55,335
- What happens now?
- You need a bronchoscopy.

72
00:03:56,169 --> 00:03:58,247
We put a camera down your throat
to see how much damage there is,

73
00:03:58,271 --> 00:03:59,711
and what we need
to do to repair it.

74
00:04:00,207 --> 00:04:01,903
But don't worry,
you'll be sedated.

75
00:04:02,008 --> 00:04:03,032
Please don't.

76
00:04:03,276 --> 00:04:05,939
Oh, I'm sorry, the test
is absolutely necessary.

77
00:04:06,213 --> 00:04:09,445
The test is fine. But,
please don't touch me.

78
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:11,111
Except for medical purposes.

79
00:04:11,551 --> 00:04:12,575
Yeah, of course.

80
00:04:18,225 --> 00:04:20,956
That does not make sense.

81
00:04:22,062 --> 00:04:23,963
A number of religions
have rules about touching.

82
00:04:24,064 --> 00:04:26,226
- I don't quite get it, but...
- That makes sense.

83
00:04:26,299 --> 00:04:29,633
People shouldn't touch people
unless there is a very good reason.

84
00:04:30,203 --> 00:04:32,638
Okay, then what
doesn't make sense?

85
00:04:33,807 --> 00:04:35,400
The grease fire.

86
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:37,904
The grease fire
explains the whole thing.

87
00:04:37,978 --> 00:04:39,139
The burn, the smoke.

88
00:04:39,312 --> 00:04:42,771
She told us she forgot
the stove was hot.

89
00:04:42,916 --> 00:04:45,818
How can you forget
something's hot when it is on fire?

90
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,731
Shaun, I'm sure we would
have heard more of the story

91
00:04:48,755 --> 00:04:51,155
if she hadn't suddenly thought
she was having a heart attack.

92
00:04:57,063 --> 00:04:58,395
Why didn't you fire him?

93
00:04:58,632 --> 00:05:00,243
Because his story
was different than yours.

94
00:05:00,267 --> 00:05:01,307
And you believe his story?

95
00:05:03,103 --> 00:05:04,332
I believe your story.

96
00:05:04,938 --> 00:05:06,463
But you can't prove it,

97
00:05:06,573 --> 00:05:09,737
and we simply can't make a
policy of believing every woman

98
00:05:09,810 --> 00:05:11,574
who files a complaint
against every man.

99
00:05:14,347 --> 00:05:16,646
After a few thousand
years of doing the opposite,

100
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:18,184
it wouldn't kill
us to overcorrect.

101
00:05:18,418 --> 00:05:20,096
And the fact that your
boyfriend assaulted him

102
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,816
took away any leverage I had.

103
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:23,620
I did what I could.

104
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:26,990
I got him to take a position
where he has very little contact

105
00:05:27,093 --> 00:05:28,356
with staff, with patients.

106
00:05:28,461 --> 00:05:29,485
Outreach chair.

107
00:05:29,696 --> 00:05:31,164
And it's a lousy assignment.

108
00:05:31,364 --> 00:05:32,684
Sooner or later,
he's gonna quit.

109
00:05:33,366 --> 00:05:34,959
And get a job somewhere else.

110
00:05:35,769 --> 00:05:37,431
If you have any better ideas,

111
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:41,372
I look forward to hearing them.

112
00:05:53,286 --> 00:05:54,366
You're very lucky.

113
00:05:56,623 --> 00:05:58,888
The aneurysm was in a
small communicating artery.

114
00:05:59,292 --> 00:06:01,772
We were able to restore blood
flow to the impacted brain areas.

115
00:06:01,895 --> 00:06:02,954
He's gonna be okay.

116
00:06:03,063 --> 00:06:04,122
Thank God.

117
00:06:09,336 --> 00:06:12,135
Is this what life is gonna
be like from now on?

118
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:14,970
Are these things just
going to keep happening?

119
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:17,006
We're gonna keep
him here for a few days,

120
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:18,371
do some follow-up testing,

121
00:06:18,478 --> 00:06:20,640
make some adjustments
to his medications.

122
00:06:21,348 --> 00:06:23,408
Hopefully we'll find
out why this happened.

123
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:27,744
I have to go.

124
00:06:30,924 --> 00:06:32,668
- Another one?
- Post-operative imaging showed

125
00:06:32,692 --> 00:06:35,526
a 26 millimeter aneurysm
in the basilar artery.

126
00:06:35,662 --> 00:06:36,686
That size and location,

127
00:06:36,763 --> 00:06:38,323
we're looking at a
high risk of rupture.

128
00:06:38,365 --> 00:06:40,061
He must have a
genetic predisposition.

129
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:41,929
Maybe a
connective-tissue disease.

130
00:06:42,202 --> 00:06:43,670
All academic till we repair it.

131
00:06:45,705 --> 00:06:46,816
Through the pharynx

132
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:49,002
and over to grandmother's
house we go.

133
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:51,704
There's the epiglottis
and the vocal cords.

134
00:06:53,213 --> 00:06:55,133
I know you're not happy
that I sued the hospital,

135
00:06:55,715 --> 00:06:57,195
but I'm not gonna
apologize for that.

136
00:06:57,684 --> 00:06:58,708
That makes it simple.

137
00:06:59,386 --> 00:07:00,945
I did it because I
want to be here.

138
00:07:01,388 --> 00:07:03,857
I believe I can learn a lot from
you. Even from your doghouse.

139
00:07:05,125 --> 00:07:06,605
I just hope you give
me a chance, sir.

140
00:07:07,460 --> 00:07:08,519
There's the carina.

141
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:12,196
I'm gonna pass into the
mainstem bronchus of the left lung.

142
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:15,463
Is breaking up with
your fiancÃ©e traumatic?

143
00:07:19,239 --> 00:07:20,730
When I saw a woman get shot,

144
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:24,438
everyone told me it was traumatic
and that I should be going home.

145
00:07:24,945 --> 00:07:26,140
Should you be going home?

146
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:29,408
Give me a mucosal brush

147
00:07:29,482 --> 00:07:31,280
- for a cellular sample.
- Loading it now.

148
00:07:31,384 --> 00:07:34,445
How long does it take to get over a
breakup with the woman you love?

149
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:39,391
I'm seeing a lot of inflammation,
but no smoke damage.

150
00:07:39,926 --> 00:07:41,588
That makes sense.

151
00:07:41,828 --> 00:07:43,472
I thought we were doing this
because she inhaled smoke?

152
00:07:43,496 --> 00:07:47,331
She said she inhaled
smoke. I didn't believe her.

153
00:07:47,567 --> 00:07:50,046
Whatever the cause, the
inflammation and the damage are real.

154
00:07:50,070 --> 00:07:51,561
Let's get a mucosal biopsy.

155
00:07:52,105 --> 00:07:53,334
If I move down here...

156
00:07:55,108 --> 00:07:56,485
The scope breached
a bronchial wall.

157
00:07:56,509 --> 00:07:58,603
- She's hemorrhaging.
- This is bad.

158
00:07:58,678 --> 00:07:59,737
Prep the OR.

159
00:07:59,913 --> 00:08:02,314
Type and cross two units
of blood. We've gotta move.

160
00:08:05,285 --> 00:08:06,565
We know there was a burn.

161
00:08:06,619 --> 00:08:08,952
Was it something
related to the grease fire,

162
00:08:09,022 --> 00:08:10,684
or a separate,
coincidental injury?

163
00:08:15,362 --> 00:08:16,830
You don't have a theory?

164
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:19,024
Or are you refusing
to talk to Jared?

165
00:08:19,132 --> 00:08:20,732
I didn't answer
because it doesn't matter

166
00:08:20,767 --> 00:08:22,087
until we can
repair this puncture

167
00:08:22,135 --> 00:08:24,604
before bacteria passes
through and spreads an infection.

168
00:08:25,005 --> 00:08:26,029
That's true.

169
00:08:26,139 --> 00:08:27,198
Cut this suture.

170
00:08:27,307 --> 00:08:29,173
Let's approximate
the edges with forceps.

171
00:08:29,542 --> 00:08:31,272
Are you and Jared even now?

172
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:35,543
He made a mistake, so did you.

173
00:08:35,648 --> 00:08:37,173
Exactly what mistake did I make?

174
00:08:37,283 --> 00:08:39,445
This breach was your fault.

175
00:08:41,388 --> 00:08:42,720
Is that traumatic?

176
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:52,525
I had breakfast by myself.

177
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:53,823
Where were you?

178
00:08:54,067 --> 00:08:56,387
I'm sorry. Were we supposed
to have breakfast this morning?

179
00:08:56,469 --> 00:08:57,493
I had an early consult.

180
00:08:57,737 --> 00:09:01,367
Yes. We always have
breakfast on Mondays.

181
00:09:01,741 --> 00:09:03,471
- We do?
- Every Monday.

182
00:09:04,010 --> 00:09:05,308
Every Monday.

183
00:09:05,412 --> 00:09:06,471
Thank you.

184
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:10,547
Well, I guess our streak
has been broken then, huh?

185
00:09:11,151 --> 00:09:13,518
If someone punctures
the bronchus

186
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:16,747
during a routine bronchoscopy,
that's a mistake, right?

187
00:09:17,023 --> 00:09:19,686
Well, I can't imagine
how it wouldn't be.

188
00:09:19,759 --> 00:09:21,159
Why? What did you do, Shaun?

189
00:09:21,327 --> 00:09:24,661
I'm wondering if I need
to report Dr. Melendez.

190
00:09:25,265 --> 00:09:26,824
Dr. Melendez did that?

191
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:28,698
The protocol is very clear.

192
00:09:29,035 --> 00:09:30,435
I need to report it.

193
00:09:31,838 --> 00:09:35,240
But I've seen how
Jared is being treated.

194
00:09:35,341 --> 00:09:38,778
Will Dr. Melendez treat
me badly if I report this?

195
00:09:40,747 --> 00:09:43,376
He shouldn't, obviously. But
human nature being what...

196
00:09:45,552 --> 00:09:46,611
Human nature?

197
00:09:49,556 --> 00:09:52,287
Shaun, you know what? You
should make this decision for yourself.

198
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:59,395
In fact, you should make

199
00:09:59,466 --> 00:10:01,765
all your decisions
yourself from here on in.

200
00:10:02,802 --> 00:10:05,795
That's what we agreed on, right?

201
00:10:11,778 --> 00:10:14,373
Have you considered an
endovascular embolization procedure?

202
00:10:14,547 --> 00:10:17,608
I have. It's a little less risky,
but I haven't done as many.

203
00:10:17,717 --> 00:10:19,777
So, I'm not sure which
way we're better off.

204
00:10:20,153 --> 00:10:21,263
You want me to check the roster?

205
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:23,447
See if there's somebody
available with more experience?

206
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:25,148
I would like to assist, but yes.

207
00:10:27,393 --> 00:10:28,417
Okay, here we go.

208
00:10:30,763 --> 00:10:31,890
No, he's not available.

209
00:10:32,565 --> 00:10:33,624
So make him available.

210
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,059
I got a husband and father

211
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:37,297
who presented with two
aneurysms in the last 12 hours.

212
00:10:38,505 --> 00:10:40,269
I'd rather not. This
particular surgeon

213
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:43,572
was recently transferred.

214
00:10:48,581 --> 00:10:49,605
Not a chance.

215
00:10:50,917 --> 00:10:54,149
Coyle is the best available
surgeon for the job.

216
00:10:54,254 --> 00:10:55,586
Coyle should have been fired.

217
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:57,466
And if he'd been fired,
he wouldn't be available.

218
00:10:57,490 --> 00:10:58,570
And if he wasn't available,

219
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:00,225
you would be the
best person for the job.

220
00:11:01,628 --> 00:11:03,324
Our ultimate duty
is to the patient.

221
00:11:05,999 --> 00:11:07,023
No, it's not.

222
00:11:08,601 --> 00:11:10,041
You agree he should
have been fired?

223
00:11:10,537 --> 00:11:12,314
- Of course...
- Even if he was the best doctor

224
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:14,298
in the hospital, he should
have been fired, right?

225
00:11:15,041 --> 00:11:16,100
Yes.

226
00:11:16,176 --> 00:11:19,203
So some things have to matter
more than who is the most skilled.

227
00:11:20,446 --> 00:11:22,938
If we forgive Coyle just
because he's good at something,

228
00:11:23,149 --> 00:11:24,515
what does he do next?

229
00:11:25,818 --> 00:11:27,616
Either he matters, or we matter.

230
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:39,161
Were you upset
during the procedure?

231
00:11:40,867 --> 00:11:42,836
Did Murphy tell you
that I was traumatized?

232
00:11:43,736 --> 00:11:45,514
You think that I might
have almost killed a person

233
00:11:45,538 --> 00:11:46,631
because you dumped me?

234
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:48,884
The fact that you're
describing it as me dumping you

235
00:11:48,908 --> 00:11:50,536
suggests that you are upset.

236
00:11:51,844 --> 00:11:55,542
Look, I'm fine, you're
fine, nobody's upset.

237
00:11:55,748 --> 00:11:56,807
Great.

238
00:11:57,984 --> 00:12:00,647
But you do understand that I
have to ask you these questions?

239
00:12:01,020 --> 00:12:02,648
That I need a
statement from you?

240
00:12:03,823 --> 00:12:05,382
Yes. Here's my statement.

241
00:12:06,192 --> 00:12:08,559
I wasn't distracted.
I didn't screw up.

242
00:12:09,095 --> 00:12:10,154
Did you get all that?

243
00:12:20,873 --> 00:12:22,585
Your bronchus was
punctured during the procedure,

244
00:12:22,609 --> 00:12:25,943
- but it's been repaired.
- How? How could that happen?

245
00:12:26,379 --> 00:12:27,574
Why did you lie?

246
00:12:27,914 --> 00:12:31,544
You said that you inhaled smoke,
but there was no evidence of smoke.

247
00:12:32,018 --> 00:12:34,078
So, what do you gain
by lying to your doctors?

248
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:38,585
I wasn't lying. I was
just confused, I guess.

249
00:12:39,125 --> 00:12:42,027
I was in a lot of pain and it
was all happening so fast.

250
00:12:43,696 --> 00:12:44,720
My stomach...

251
00:12:44,964 --> 00:12:46,762
