505
00:28:40,352 --> 00:28:41,911
His BP was stable going in.

506
00:28:42,588 --> 00:28:43,965
He's been on calcium
channel blockers

507
00:28:43,989 --> 00:28:45,833
- the last six years...
- Well, we missed something.

508
00:28:45,857 --> 00:28:47,553
BP doesn't skyrocket
for no reason.

509
00:28:49,728 --> 00:28:50,752
Run a full workup.

510
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:54,859
Why would a 28-year-old

511
00:28:54,933 --> 00:28:56,868
with no risk factors
have a heart attack?

512
00:28:57,502 --> 00:28:58,663
Mm.

513
00:28:58,904 --> 00:29:00,099
Her heart is burning.

514
00:29:01,873 --> 00:29:02,897
Burning?

515
00:29:03,008 --> 00:29:04,374
From the caustic chemical.

516
00:29:04,743 --> 00:29:07,838
- Murphy...
- It's going through her system.

517
00:29:08,180 --> 00:29:12,015
Unlike thermal burns, chemical
burns get worse over time.

518
00:29:12,384 --> 00:29:15,286
And it also explains
the punctured bronchus.

519
00:29:15,387 --> 00:29:17,515
The caustic chemical
thinned the bronchial walls.

520
00:29:17,689 --> 00:29:19,248
You did not make a mistake.

521
00:29:19,691 --> 00:29:20,971
That's not the only explanation.

522
00:29:22,561 --> 00:29:23,620
But I'll shut up now.

523
00:29:24,129 --> 00:29:26,849
You think you have a good idea,
but you're going to shut yourself up?

524
00:29:28,467 --> 00:29:31,528
It could be caused by an infection
from the bacteria that leaked,

525
00:29:31,970 --> 00:29:33,461
as a result of the puncture.

526
00:29:34,072 --> 00:29:37,634
The treatments are
diametrically opposed.

527
00:29:37,743 --> 00:29:42,204
Antibiotics if it's infection,
steroids if it's inflammation.

528
00:29:42,281 --> 00:29:45,251
If we give antibiotics and
she needs steroids instead,

529
00:29:45,317 --> 00:29:46,717
it will suppress
her immune system,

530
00:29:46,752 --> 00:29:48,653
causing the infection
to flourish and kill her.

531
00:29:49,087 --> 00:29:52,216
If she needs steroids and
we give her antibiotics, then...

532
00:29:52,291 --> 00:29:55,489
- I get it, we better be right.
- Yes.

533
00:29:56,061 --> 00:29:58,792
Sir, I think we should bring
another senior attending in

534
00:29:58,897 --> 00:30:00,957
- to consult on this decision.
- Why?

535
00:30:01,066 --> 00:30:02,786
Because if Shaun's
right, you're exonerated.

536
00:30:03,302 --> 00:30:04,712
And if I'm right, you may
have made the mistake

537
00:30:04,736 --> 00:30:05,816
that could kill this woman.

538
00:30:07,839 --> 00:30:09,239
You don't think I
can be objective?

539
00:30:09,274 --> 00:30:11,072
I think you're
incredibly professional...

540
00:30:11,143 --> 00:30:12,167
Shut up, Jared.

541
00:30:16,181 --> 00:30:19,413
It is possible
that I screwed up.

542
00:30:22,487 --> 00:30:24,207
Let's put her on broad
spectrum antibiotics.

543
00:30:24,790 --> 00:30:25,917
You're wrong.

544
00:30:26,792 --> 00:30:31,025
Making a decision on the assumption
you made a mistake is a mistake.

545
00:30:31,697 --> 00:30:33,097
You're very arrogant.

546
00:30:34,766 --> 00:30:37,031
It helps you be a great surgeon.

547
00:30:39,271 --> 00:30:41,103
Fortunately, I don't
need your approval.

548
00:30:52,017 --> 00:30:54,680
We've determined what
the underlying problem was.

549
00:30:55,153 --> 00:30:56,993
What caused your husband's
aneurysm to rupture,

550
00:30:57,022 --> 00:30:59,184
and why his blood
pressure spiked in the OR.

551
00:30:59,291 --> 00:31:01,851
According to his labs, he
hasn't been taking his meds.

552
00:31:02,728 --> 00:31:04,162
As far as I know, he has.

553
00:31:04,229 --> 00:31:06,221
I mean, that's
just not like him.

554
00:31:07,065 --> 00:31:08,505
We don't think
it's like him either.

555
00:31:11,570 --> 00:31:13,903
You think I had
something to do with this?

556
00:31:14,639 --> 00:31:15,663
That I what?

557
00:31:16,241 --> 00:31:17,300
Threw his meds away?

558
00:31:18,543 --> 00:31:19,636
He'd just order more.

559
00:31:20,979 --> 00:31:22,743
But if you emptied his capsules

560
00:31:22,981 --> 00:31:26,145
and filled them with
sugar, or even better, salt...

561
00:31:27,319 --> 00:31:28,651
It would end your nightmare.

562
00:31:32,157 --> 00:31:33,853
I was willing to let him die.

563
00:31:35,060 --> 00:31:36,084
But I could never...

564
00:31:40,599 --> 00:31:43,330
If I were strong
enough to kill him...

565
00:31:55,247 --> 00:31:58,411
Is there a chance your son
knows more than you think he does?

566
00:32:20,539 --> 00:32:21,563
Her heart rate's 90.

567
00:32:21,807 --> 00:32:23,605
That's in the normal range.

568
00:32:23,775 --> 00:32:26,040
But it was 83. It
should be going down.

569
00:32:26,378 --> 00:32:28,711
All her other signs are normal.

570
00:32:29,047 --> 00:32:31,881
You were right, this
is the proper treatment.

571
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:32,974
Ninety-five.

572
00:32:36,888 --> 00:32:38,088
I'm switching her to steroids.

573
00:32:38,990 --> 00:32:42,791
If we give her steroids, it will
suppress her immune system,

574
00:32:42,894 --> 00:32:44,238
causing the
infection to flourish...

575
00:32:44,262 --> 00:32:46,240
I'm gonna push 40 milligrams
of methylprednisolone.

576
00:32:46,264 --> 00:32:47,391
And she'll die.

577
00:32:49,067 --> 00:32:50,091
This is on me.

578
00:32:50,969 --> 00:32:51,993
I know.

579
00:33:00,779 --> 00:33:02,907
We switched her to
methylprednisolone.

580
00:33:04,349 --> 00:33:05,408
It's working.

581
00:33:05,851 --> 00:33:07,012
You were wrong.

582
00:33:07,419 --> 00:33:08,478
Yeah, I got that.

583
00:33:09,020 --> 00:33:11,512
Just about the treatment choice.
You didn't do anything wrong

584
00:33:11,623 --> 00:33:12,921
- in the OR.
- Don't kiss my ass.

585
00:33:14,025 --> 00:33:16,153
Jared saved her life.

586
00:33:18,296 --> 00:33:20,595
If he hadn't acted so
quickly, she would've died

587
00:33:20,665 --> 00:33:22,463
and that would've
been your fault.

588
00:33:23,335 --> 00:33:25,634
- Yes, it would've.
- You should thank him.

589
00:33:33,211 --> 00:33:34,839
Thank you, Dr. Kalu.

590
00:34:30,068 --> 00:34:31,434
Hey. Can I help you?

591
00:34:32,270 --> 00:34:34,535
I'm Dr. Shaun Murphy.

592
00:34:35,106 --> 00:34:37,905
You're my new
neighbor. Number 34.

593
00:34:39,578 --> 00:34:40,602
Yeah. Cool.

594
00:34:42,747 --> 00:34:44,307
- Do you wanna come in for a beer?
- No.

595
00:34:52,357 --> 00:34:53,381
Nice work.

596
00:34:54,459 --> 00:34:55,518
You, too.

597
00:34:56,227 --> 00:34:57,422
You can have the honors.

598
00:35:00,031 --> 00:35:01,966
This is the first time
I'm not looking forward

599
00:35:02,067 --> 00:35:03,933
to telling the
family it went well.

600
00:35:31,396 --> 00:35:32,557
You're going to be fine.

601
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:34,224
The treatment worked?

602
00:35:35,500 --> 00:35:37,992
The second one did. The
first one almost killed you.

603
00:35:38,770 --> 00:35:40,648
The fact that you're
alive right now is evidence

604
00:35:40,672 --> 00:35:42,316
that you were working
with dimethyl sulfate.

605
00:35:42,340 --> 00:35:44,775
You're a terrorist, aren't you?

606
00:35:47,312 --> 00:35:49,941
My brother works
for a drug company.

607
00:35:50,515 --> 00:35:53,644
They use dimethyl sulfate to
make one of their medications.

608
00:35:53,818 --> 00:35:54,842
He stole some for me.

609
00:35:54,953 --> 00:35:57,149
So you could make
a chemical weapon.

610
00:35:57,489 --> 00:35:59,321
So I could make perfume.

611
00:36:04,129 --> 00:36:05,153
Smell that.

612
00:36:18,376 --> 00:36:19,537
It's beautiful.

613
00:36:21,479 --> 00:36:23,038
But very stupid.

614
00:36:23,281 --> 00:36:24,305
Yeah.

615
00:36:24,949 --> 00:36:28,716
Especially since my brother would
get fired if anyone ever found out.

616
00:36:30,889 --> 00:36:31,948
You believe her?

617
00:36:32,290 --> 00:36:33,656
Protecting someone.

618
00:36:34,059 --> 00:36:35,322
Reason number three.

619
00:36:38,697 --> 00:36:40,063
So, we good?

620
00:36:41,466 --> 00:36:43,110
The thing is, I'm not
sure it really matters.

621
00:36:43,134 --> 00:36:45,374
I've been told I can only
have three residents next year.

622
00:36:45,704 --> 00:36:47,502
- That's great.
- Not really.

623
00:36:47,706 --> 00:36:50,005
Because of Coyle's
transfer, I have to take on his.

624
00:36:51,309 --> 00:36:52,333
Reznick?

625
00:36:53,812 --> 00:36:54,836
She's a pain.

626
00:36:55,346 --> 00:36:56,974
Pain can be a
hell of a motivator.

627
00:36:57,682 --> 00:36:58,706
Good luck.

628
00:37:05,390 --> 00:37:06,414
You were right.

629
00:37:09,194 --> 00:37:11,493
And I think you were right
that I wanted you to be wrong.

630
00:37:13,364 --> 00:37:14,388
And I'm sorry.

631
00:37:16,067 --> 00:37:17,091
You were right, too.

632
00:37:19,571 --> 00:37:21,733
I kept telling myself
that I'm fine, but,

633
00:37:23,274 --> 00:37:24,333
it's been hard.

634
00:37:25,376 --> 00:37:26,901
Got me second-guessing myself,

635
00:37:27,011 --> 00:37:30,038
maybe affecting my
judgment, I don't know.

636
00:37:32,016 --> 00:37:34,178
If we're hurting so bad,
maybe we made a mistake.

637
00:37:37,722 --> 00:37:38,746
No.

638
00:37:39,090 --> 00:37:40,718
It just means that
what we had mattered.

639
00:37:41,459 --> 00:37:42,819
It doesn't mean
that it was right.

640
00:37:44,763 --> 00:37:46,129
I've also been thinking that

641
00:37:47,265 --> 00:37:49,359
arrogance does make
me a better surgeon.

642
00:37:51,803 --> 00:37:53,523
But it's not gonna make
me a better husband.

643
00:37:57,275 --> 00:37:58,299
I'm sorry.

644
00:38:11,055 --> 00:38:12,079
Kristin?

645
00:38:13,224 --> 00:38:14,920
Hey, I'm Claire.

646
00:38:14,993 --> 00:38:16,723
Hi. Thanks.

647
00:38:21,499 --> 00:38:25,231
I am doing some
research on Dr. Coyle.

648
00:38:26,805 --> 00:38:30,003
On the women who worked
with him and then quit.

649
00:38:31,676 --> 00:38:33,338
I got another offer at SF Muni.

650
00:38:37,081 --> 00:38:39,448
I was harassed by Dr. Coyle.

651
00:38:41,619 --> 00:38:43,281
And I think you were, too.

652
00:38:56,301 --> 00:38:59,328
Doing the right thing can
make things a little better.

653
00:39:02,173 --> 00:39:03,698
Especially if we do it together.

654
00:39:08,213 --> 00:39:09,272
Yeah.

655
00:39:26,231 --> 00:39:27,631
I have a new neighbor.

656
00:39:28,833 --> 00:39:32,292
Hmm. So, Lea's really gone, huh?

657
00:39:33,504 --> 00:39:36,030
So, can we have
breakfast tomorrow?

658
00:39:37,976 --> 00:39:40,138
I'd love to, Shaun, but...

659
00:39:44,215 --> 00:39:45,239
We, um...

660
00:39:45,383 --> 00:39:46,851
We talked about this, right?

661
00:39:47,218 --> 00:39:52,316
I said that I would back
off if you stayed, right?

662
00:39:52,390 --> 00:39:54,916
- More space, less fathering?
- I don't need a father,

663
00:39:55,026 --> 00:39:56,426
I hate fathers.

664
00:39:56,594 --> 00:39:59,063
- Right, so...
- I need a friend.

665
00:40:04,235 --> 00:40:09,071
Shaun, I am someone who
can't help but give advice.

666
00:40:09,240 --> 00:40:12,768
You know, I don't
know if I can not do that.

667
00:40:15,747 --> 00:40:19,343
So, you think I can
change and you can't?

668
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:24,419
I think that we have a
certain kind of relationship,

669
00:40:25,256 --> 00:40:27,521
and we can call it
something different if we want,

670
00:40:27,592 --> 00:40:30,084
but we can't magically
make it different.

671
00:40:30,962 --> 00:40:34,023
You said that you wanted space,
you said that you needed space.

672
00:40:41,406 --> 00:40:44,137
I think you should be my friend.

673
00:40:51,616 --> 00:40:52,640
Shaun...

674
00:41:07,332 --> 00:41:08,391
Okay.

675
00:41:12,270 --> 00:41:13,294
Shaun...

676
00:42:00,451 --> 00:42:03,011
<i>What are you smelling right now?</i>

677
00:42:05,023 --> 00:42:06,150
Pine trees.

678
00:42:08,726 --> 00:42:09,955
Mm.
